Happy Endings is an American television sitcom which premiered on ABC on April 13, 2011

Plot:
----------
Happy Endings follows the dysfunctional adventures of six best friends living in Chicago: &quot;crazy-in-love&quot; married couple, businessman overachiever Brad (Damon Wayans Jr.) and type-A control freak Jane (Eliza Coupe); ditzy Alex (Elisha Cuthbert), a happy-go-lucky boutique owner and Jane's younger sister; daydreamer Dave (Zachary Knighton), an aspiring restaurateur and food truck owner who used to be engaged to Alex; slacker manchild Max (Adam Pally), who deals with trying to hold a job and maintaining a consistent relationship; and klutzy serial dating single girl Penny (Casey Wilson), who fears she's forever doomed for spinsterhood.


